"It is expected that there will be 26.8 thousand college graduates in the Beijing area in 2022 - Xinhua News Agency"
"According to a recent video conference on the employment and entrepreneurship of 2022 college graduates in Beijing held by the Beijing Municipal Education Commission and the Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau, it was learned that the number of college graduates in the Beijing area in 2022 is expected to reach 26.8 thousand, an increase of 16 thousand from last year."
"The relevant officials from the Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau stated that they will deploy the employment work of college graduates in Beijing from various aspects, such as enhancing the match of supply and demand, strengthening policy support, expanding employment channels, ensuring assistance for those in difficulty, supporting innovation and entrepreneurship, and improving service efficiency."
"The reporter learned that the Beijing Human Resources and Social Security Bureau will build a practical platform, increase job supply, actively contact 40 college graduate workplace experience bases, visit employers, integrate demand information and job information; focus on "six batches", that is, expanding the recruitment of a batch of institutions, expanding the recruitment of a batch of state-owned enterprises, expanding the recruitment of a batch of grass-roots projects, expanding the recruitment of a batch of conscripts, expanding the employment and internship retention of a batch, and expanding the employment driven by entrepreneurship of a batch; implementing the "life-long policy" dynamic management, recommending not less than 5 job information for each graduate, and ensuring that 100% of the difficult families with graduation students who have the intention to be employed will be assisted."